author: Karin Boye
quote: "As twilight falls, the stars appear,"
subject: Scandinavian Nature Poetry (Late 19th century)
permalink: /Scandinavian Nature Poetry (Late 19th century)/Karin Boye/Karin Boye - Twilights Lullaby
---

As twilight falls, the stars appear,
To sprinkle light across the eastern shore,
The gentle waves keep whispering near,
A lullaby forevermore.

With every breath, the night unfolds,
A tapestry of dreams,
Where wishes dance on starlit paths,
And hope forever gleams.

- Karin Boye
